OL,3,CAssisted dying bill moves one step
OL,4,Ccloser to becoming legal in the Isle
OL,5,Cof Man
OL,7,FAs it stands, the Bill is only for
OL,8,Fadults who have been resident on the
OL,9,Fisland for five years, have a terminal
OL,10,Fillness with a life expectancy of no
OL,11,Fmore than 12 months, and who have a
OL,12,Fsettled intention to end their life.
OL,14,FOther measures around ensuring legal
OL,15,Fand workplace protection for medical
OL,16,Fprofessionals who participate in
OL,17,Fassisted dying have also been agreed,
OL,18,Fwhile a request from the British
OL,19,FMedical Association (BMA) for an opt-
OL,20,Fin model for doctors who choose to be
OL,21,Fpart of the service was approved.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
