OL,7,FHe said debate has been thorough and
OL,8,Fthat, while he respects the views of
OL,9,Fthose who remain opposed to change,
OL,10,Fthere is a "significant majority of
OL,11,FMembers who are now content with the
OL,12,Fway the Bill has been changed to agree
OL,13,Fa third reading".
OL,15,FHe added: "We certainly are still in
OL,16,Fthe position of being the first
OL,17,F(place) in the British Isles to bring
OL,18,Flegislation forward for royal assent.
