OL,3,CAssisted dying bill moves one step
OL,4,Ccloser to becoming legal in the Isle
OL,5,Cof Man
OL,7,F"But there will need to be quite a
OL,8,Flong implementation period, including
OL,9,Fconversations and working with people
OL,10,Flike the General Medical Council (GMC)
OL,11,Fand the BMA to make this Bill
OL,12,Foperational."
OL,14,FCampaigners opposed to a change in the
OL,15,Flaw have voiced concerns that
OL,16,Flegalising assisted dying could put
OL,17,Fpressure on vulnerable people to end
OL,18,Ftheir lives for fear of being a burden
OL,19,Fon others, and argue that the
OL,20,Fdisabled, elderly, sick or depressed
OL,21,Fcould be especially at risk.
